This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to identify frequent user utterances and corresponding agent responses in conversations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel clustering algorithm, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to align the clusters, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with analyzing the performance of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
